<sec>
<st>
N series</st>
<p>

<image location="right" width="150px" src="Renfe_269_escalaN.jpg" type="thumb">
<caption>

Ibertren Renfe class 269 NScale
</caption>
</image>

Ibertren manufactured two series of N-scale models: 2N and 3N.</p>
<p>

In the 3N series, a non-insulated <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../713/47713.xml">
DC</link> <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../655/677655.xml">
three-rail system</link> was used to power the engines. The 2N series, which were introduced later when 3N sales went down, used DC with negative current on one rail and positive on the other.</p>

